The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) has honoured the Chairman of Badagry West Local Council Development Area of Lagos, Joseph Gbenu, as ambassador of war against drug abuse. Narcotic Commander Seme Special Area Command Abubakar Wada said the honour was in recognition of the chairman’s assistance and contributions to the war against drug abuse. The decoration was in commemoration of the 2022 International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking. Wada said Gbenu assisted the agency by providing it with a conducive environment to operate on roads and waterways in Seme. On the achievements of NDLEA, he said 40 people were arrested within the period, comprising 31 men and nine women.   Bill to increase retirement age for people with disability…     Oyo students to represent Nigeria in Switzerland after…     Alleged fraud: Okorocha seeks court’s permission to travel…   He said 19 of them were convicted, while 20 were counselled. Gbenu said abuse of drugs was assuming a frightening and worrisome dimension. He urged stakeholders to ensure the menace was stopped. Gbenu thanked NDLEA for giving him the award, noting that he would not disappoint the agency. The Alapa of Apa kingdom, Oba Oyekan Ajose, advised youths to shun drug abuse. Mr David Aladeotan, the coordinator, National Youth Council of Nigeria (NYCN), said youths at borders should be cautious because of the menace of drug abuse.